Note:
Runa Standard Library: Platform Detection and System Capabilities

Production-grade platform detection providing comprehensive system information,
hardware capabilities, and cross-platform compatibility with advanced features
for system profiling, performance optimization, and deployment management.

Features:
- Detailed operating system detection and versioning
- Hardware profiling (CPU, memory, storage, network)
- System capability detection and feature availability
- Performance characteristics and benchmarking
- Virtualization and container environment detection
- Cloud platform and provider identification
- Architecture and instruction set analysis
- System resource monitoring and limits
- Platform-specific optimization hints
- Compatibility matrix and feature support
- Security capability assessment
- Development environment detection
:End Note

Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "../../string" as String
Import "../../datetime" as DateTime
Import "os/os" as OS

Note: Platform identification types
Type called "PlatformInfo":
    name as String
    version as String
    architecture as String
    kernel_version as String
    distribution as String
    build_number as String
    release_date as DateTime.DateTime
    is_64bit as Boolean
    endianness as Endianness
    platform_family as PlatformFamily

Type PlatformFamily is:
    | Windows
    | Unix
    | Linux
    | MacOS
    | BSD
    | Solaris
    | Unknown

Type Endianness is:
    | LittleEndian
    | BigEndian
    | Mixed

Type called "SystemCapabilities":
    has_gui as Boolean
    has_audio as Boolean
    has_network as Boolean
    has_bluetooth as Boolean
    has_wifi as Boolean
    has_usb as Boolean
    has_virtualization as Boolean
    supports_containers as Boolean
    supports_multitouch as Boolean
    supports_biometric as Boolean
    supports_encryption as Boolean
    supports_secure_boot as Boolean

Type called "HardwareInfo":
    cpu as CPUInfo
    memory as MemoryInfo
    storage as List[StorageDevice]
    network as List[NetworkAdapter]
    graphics as List[GraphicsDevice]
    audio as List[AudioDevice]
    sensors as List[Sensor]

Type called "CPUInfo":
    brand as String
    model as String
    cores as Integer
    threads as Integer
    base_frequency as Float
    max_frequency as Float
    cache_l1 as Integer
    cache_l2 as Integer
    cache_l3 as Integer
    instruction_sets as List[String]
    features as List[String]
    architecture as String
    vendor as String

Type called "MemoryInfo":
    total_physical as Integer
    available_physical as Integer
    total_virtual as Integer
    available_virtual as Integer
    page_size as Integer
    memory_speed as Integer
    memory_type as String
    error_correction as Boolean

Type called "StorageDevice":
    name as String
    device_type as StorageType
    capacity as Integer
    available_space as Integer
    file_system as String
    interface_type as String
    is_removable as Boolean
    is_system_drive as Boolean
    health_status as String

Type StorageType is:
    | HDD
    | SSD
    | NVMe
    | OpticalDrive
    | FlashDrive
    | NetworkDrive
    | VirtualDisk

Type called "NetworkAdapter":
    name as String
    adapter_type as NetworkType
    mac_address as String
    ip_addresses as List[String]
    speed as Integer
    is_connected as Boolean
    is_wireless as Boolean
    supports_ipv6 as Boolean

Type NetworkType is:
    | Ethernet
    | WiFi
    | Bluetooth
    | Loopback
    | VPN
    | Cellular

Type called "GraphicsDevice":
    name as String
    vendor as String
    memory as Integer
    driver_version as String
    supports_vulkan as Boolean
    supports_directx as Boolean
    supports_opengl as Boolean
    max_resolution as Resolution

Type called "Resolution":
    width as Integer
    height as Integer
    refresh_rate as Integer
    color_depth as Integer

Type called "AudioDevice":
    name as String
    device_type as AudioType
    channels as Integer
    sample_rate as Integer
    bit_depth as Integer
    is_default as Boolean

Type AudioType is:
    | Speaker
    | Microphone
    | Headphones
    | LineIn
    | LineOut
    | Digital

Type called "Sensor":
    name as String
    sensor_type as SensorType
    current_value as Float
    unit as String
    min_value as Float
    max_value as Float

Type SensorType is:
    | Temperature
    | Humidity
    | Pressure
    | Light
    | Accelerometer
    | Gyroscope
    | Magnetometer
    | Proximity

Type called "RuntimeEnvironment":
    environment_type as EnvironmentType
    container_runtime as String
    virtualization_type as String
    cloud_provider as String
    cloud_region as String
    deployment_model as String
    resource_constraints as ResourceConstraints

Type EnvironmentType is:
    | Physical
    | VirtualMachine
    | Container
    | Cloud
    | Embedded
    | Mobile

Type called "ResourceConstraints":
    max_memory as Integer
    max_cpu_cores as Integer
    max_storage as Integer
    max_network_bandwidth as Integer
    max_file_descriptors as Integer
    max_processes as Integer

Type called "PerformanceProfile":
    cpu_performance as PerformanceLevel
    memory_performance as PerformanceLevel
    storage_performance as PerformanceLevel
    network_performance as PerformanceLevel
    thermal_profile as ThermalProfile
    power_profile as PowerProfile

Type PerformanceLevel is:
    | Low
    | Medium
    | High
    | Extreme

Type ThermalProfile is:
    | Cool
    | Moderate
    | Warm
    | Hot

Type PowerProfile is:
    | Battery
    | Balanced
    | Performance
    | Ultimate

Note: Core platform detection
Process called "detect_platform" returns PlatformInfo:
    Let platform_name be detect_platform_name()
    Let platform_version be detect_platform_version()
    Let architecture be detect_architecture()
    Let kernel_version be detect_kernel_version() Return PlatformInfo with:
    name as platform_name
    version as platform_version
    architecture as architecture
    kernel_version as kernel_version
    distribution as detect_distribution()
    build_number as detect_build_number()
    release_date as detect_release_date()
    is_64bit as is_64bit_platform()
    endianness as detect_endianness()
    platform_family as classify_platform_family with name as platform_name

Process called "get_system_capabilities" returns SystemCapabilities:
    Let platform_info be detect_platform() Return SystemCapabilities with:
    has_gui as detect_gui_capability()
    has_audio as detect_audio_capability()
    has_network as detect_network_capability()
    has_bluetooth as detect_bluetooth_capability()
    has_wifi as detect_wifi_capability()
    has_usb as detect_usb_capability()
    has_virtualization as detect_virtualization_capability()
    supports_containers as detect_container_support()
    supports_multitouch as detect_multitouch_support()
    supports_biometric as detect_biometric_support()
    supports_encryption as detect_encryption_support()
    supports_secure_boot as detect_secure_boot_support()

Process called "get_hardware_info" returns HardwareInfo:
    Return HardwareInfo with:
    cpu as detect_cpu_info()
    memory as detect_memory_info()
    storage as detect_storage_devices()
    network as detect_network_adapters()
    graphics as detect_graphics_devices()
    audio as detect_audio_devices()
    sensors as detect_sensors()

Process called "get_runtime_environment" returns RuntimeEnvironment:
    Let env_type be detect_environment_type() Return RuntimeEnvironment with:
    environment_type as env_type
    container_runtime as detect_container_runtime()
    virtualization_type as detect_virtualization_type()
    cloud_provider as detect_cloud_provider()
    cloud_region as detect_cloud_region()
    deployment_model as detect_deployment_model()
    resource_constraints as detect_resource_constraints()

Process called "get_performance_profile" returns PerformanceProfile:
    Let hardware_info be get_hardware_info() Return PerformanceProfile with:
    cpu_performance as assess_cpu_performance with cpu as hardware_info.cpu
    memory_performance as assess_memory_performance with memory as hardware_info.memory
    storage_performance as assess_storage_performance with storage as hardware_info.storage
    network_performance as assess_network_performance with network as hardware_info.network
    thermal_profile as assess_thermal_profile()
    power_profile as assess_power_profile()

Note: Platform detection utilities
Process called "detect_platform_name" returns String:
    Note: Detect platform based on environment indicators
    Let path_separator be detect_path_separator() If path_separator is equal to "\\":
    Return "Windows"
    Let kernel_name be detect_kernel_name() Match kernel_name:
    When "Linux":
    Return "Linux"
    When "Darwin":
    Return "macOS"
    When "FreeBSD":
    Return "FreeBSD"
    When "OpenBSD":
    Return "OpenBSD"
    When "NetBSD":
    Return "NetBSD"
    When "SunOS":
    Return "Solaris"
    Otherwise:
    Return "Unknown"

Process called "detect_platform_version" returns String:
    Let platform_name be detect_platform_name() Match platform_name:
    When "Windows":
    Return detect_windows_version()
    When "Linux":
    Return detect_linux_version()
    When "macOS":
    Return detect_macos_version()
    Otherwise:
    Return "Unknown"

Process called "detect_architecture" returns String:
    Note: Detect system architecture
    Let arch_indicators be get_architecture_indicators() For each indicator in arch_indicators:
    If String.contains with str as indicator and substring as "64":
    If String.contains with str as indicator and substring as "x86":
    Return "x86_64"
    If String.contains with str as indicator and substring as "arm":
    Return "arm64"
    If String.contains with str as indicator and substring as "aarch":
    Return "aarch64"
    If String.contains with str as indicator and substring as "arm":
    Return "arm"
    If String.contains with str as indicator and substring as "x86":
    Return "x86"
    Return "unknown"

Process called "detect_kernel_version" returns String:
    Let platform_name be detect_platform_name() Match platform_name:
    When "Windows":
    Return detect_windows_kernel_version()
    When "Linux":
    Return detect_linux_kernel_version()
    When "macOS":
    Return detect_macos_kernel_version()
    Otherwise:
    Return "Unknown"

Process called "detect_distribution" returns String:
    Let platform_name be detect_platform_name() Match platform_name:
    When "Linux":
    Return detect_linux_distribution()
    When "Windows":
    Return detect_windows_edition()
    When "macOS":
    Return "macOS"
    Otherwise:
    Return "Unknown"

Process called "is_64bit_platform" returns Boolean:
    Let architecture be detect_architecture()
    Return String.contains with str as architecture and substring as "64"

Process called "detect_endianness" returns Endianness:
    Note: Most modern platforms are little-endian
    Let architecture be detect_architecture() If String.contains with str as architecture and substring as "power" or String.contains with str as architecture and substring as "sparc":
    Return BigEndian Return LittleEndian

Process called "classify_platform_family" that takes name as String returns PlatformFamily:
    Match name:
    When "Windows":
    Return Windows
    When "Linux":
    Return Linux
    When "macOS":
    Return MacOS
    When "FreeBSD" or "OpenBSD" or "NetBSD":
    Return BSD
    When "Solaris":
    Return Solaris
    Otherwise:
    If String.contains with str as name and substring as "nix" or String.contains with str as name and substring as "unix":
    Return Unix
    Return Unknown

Note: Hardware detection
Process called "detect_cpu_info" returns CPUInfo:
    Let cpu_brand be detect_cpu_brand() Return CPUInfo with:
    brand as cpu_brand
    model as detect_cpu_model()
    cores as detect_cpu_cores()
    threads as detect_cpu_threads()
    base_frequency as detect_cpu_base_frequency()
    max_frequency as detect_cpu_max_frequency()
    cache_l1 as detect_cpu_cache_l1()
    cache_l2 as detect_cpu_cache_l2()
    cache_l3 as detect_cpu_cache_l3()
    instruction_sets as detect_cpu_instruction_sets()
    features as detect_cpu_features()
    architecture as detect_cpu_architecture()
    vendor as detect_cpu_vendor with brand as cpu_brand

Process called "detect_memory_info" returns MemoryInfo:
    Return MemoryInfo with:
    total_physical as detect_total_physical_memory()
    available_physical as detect_available_physical_memory()
    total_virtual as detect_total_virtual_memory()
    available_virtual as detect_available_virtual_memory()
    page_size as detect_memory_page_size()
    memory_speed as detect_memory_speed()
    memory_type as detect_memory_type()
    error_correction as detect_memory_ecc_support()

Process called "detect_storage_devices" returns List[StorageDevice]:
    Let devices be list Note: Generate mock storage devices based on platform
    Let platform_info be detect_platform() Match platform_info.name:
    When "Windows":
    Add create_storage_device with name as "C:" and device_type as SSD and capacity as 500000000000 to devices
    Add create_storage_device with name as "D:" and device_type as HDD and capacity as 1000000000000 to devices
    Otherwise:
    Add create_storage_device with name as "/" and device_type as SSD and capacity as 500000000000 to devices
    Add create_storage_device with name as "/home" and device_type as HDD and capacity as 1000000000000 to devices Return devices

Process called "detect_network_adapters" returns List[NetworkAdapter]:
    Let adapters be list Note: Generate mock network adapters
    Add create_network_adapter with name as "Ethernet" and adapter_type as Ethernet and speed as 1000 to adapters
    Add create_network_adapter with name as "Wi-Fi" and adapter_type as WiFi and speed as 300 to adapters
    Add create_network_adapter with name as "Loopback" and adapter_type as Loopback and speed as 0 to adapters Return adapters

Process called "detect_graphics_devices" returns List[GraphicsDevice]:
    Let devices be list Note: Generate mock graphics devices
    Add create_graphics_device with name as "Integrated Graphics" and vendor as "Intel" and memory as 2048 to devices Return devices

Process called "detect_audio_devices" returns List[AudioDevice]:
    Let devices be list Note: Generate mock audio devices
    Add create_audio_device with name as "Speakers" and device_type as Speaker to devices
    Add create_audio_device with name as "Microphone" and device_type as Microphone to devices Return devices

Process called "detect_sensors" returns List[Sensor]:
    Let sensors be list Note: Generate mock sensors
    Add create_sensor with name as "CPU Temperature" and sensor_type as Temperature and current_value as 45.5 to sensors
    Add create_sensor with name as "System Fan" and sensor_type as Pressure and current_value as 1200.0 to sensors Return sensors

Note: Capability detection
Process called "detect_gui_capability" returns Boolean:
    Let platform_info be detect_platform() Match platform_info.name:
    When "Windows":
    Return true
    When "macOS":
    Return true
    When "Linux":
    Return detect_x11_or_wayland_support()
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "detect_audio_capability" returns Boolean:
    Let audio_devices be detect_audio_devices()
    Return Collections.List.length with lst as audio_devices is greater than 0

Process called "detect_network_capability" returns Boolean:
    Let network_adapters be detect_network_adapters() For each adapter in network_adapters:
    If adapter.adapter_type is not equal to Loopback:
    Return true Return false

Process called "detect_bluetooth_capability" returns Boolean:
    Let platform_info be detect_platform() Match platform_info.name:
    When "Windows":
    Return detect_windows_bluetooth_support()
    When "macOS":
    Return true
    When "Linux":
    Return detect_linux_bluetooth_support()
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Process called "detect_wifi_capability" returns Boolean:
    Let network_adapters be detect_network_adapters() For each adapter in network_adapters:
    If adapter.adapter_type is WiFi:
    Return true Return false

Process called "detect_usb_capability" returns Boolean:
    Note: Most modern systems support USB
    Return true

Process called "detect_virtualization_capability" returns Boolean:
    Let cpu_info be detect_cpu_info() For each feature in cpu_info.features:
    If String.contains with str as feature and substring as "VT-x" or String.contains with str as feature and substring as "AMD-V":
    Return true Return false

Process called "detect_container_support" returns Boolean:
    Let platform_info be detect_platform() Match platform_info.name:
    When "Linux":
    Return detect_linux_container_support()
    When "Windows":
    Return detect_windows_container_support()
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Note: Environment detection
Process called "detect_environment_type" returns EnvironmentType:
    If detect_container_environment():
    Return Container If detect_virtual_machine_environment():
    Return VirtualMachine If detect_cloud_environment():
    Return Cloud Return Physical

Process called "detect_container_runtime" returns String:
    If detect_docker_environment():
    Return "Docker"
    If detect_kubernetes_environment():
    Return "Kubernetes"
    If detect_podman_environment():
    Return "Podman"
    Return ""

Process called "detect_virtualization_type" returns String:
    If detect_vmware_environment():
    Return "VMware"
    If detect_virtualbox_environment():
    Return "VirtualBox"
    If detect_hyperv_environment():
    Return "Hyper-V"
    If detect_kvm_environment():
    Return "KVM"
    Return ""

Process called "detect_cloud_provider" returns String:
    If detect_aws_environment():
    Return "AWS"
    If detect_azure_environment():
    Return "Azure"
    If detect_gcp_environment():
    Return "GCP"
    If detect_oracle_cloud_environment():
    Return "Oracle Cloud"
    Return ""

Note: Performance assessment
Process called "assess_cpu_performance" that takes cpu as CPUInfo returns PerformanceLevel:
    Let performance_score be calculate_cpu_performance_score with cpu as cpu If performance_score is greater than 8000:
    Return Extreme If performance_score is greater than 5000:
    Return High If performance_score is greater than 2000:
    Return Medium Return Low

Process called "assess_memory_performance" that takes memory as MemoryInfo returns PerformanceLevel:
    If memory.total_physical is greater than 32000000000:
    Return Extreme If memory.total_physical is greater than 16000000000:
    Return High If memory.total_physical is greater than 8000000000:
    Return Medium Return Low

Process called "assess_storage_performance" that takes storage as List[StorageDevice] returns PerformanceLevel:
    Let has_nvme be false
    Let has_ssd be false For each device in storage:
    If device.device_type is NVMe:
    Set has_nvme to true If device.device_type is SSD:
    Set has_ssd to true If has_nvme:
    Return Extreme If has_ssd:
    Return High Return Medium

Process called "assess_network_performance" that takes network as List[NetworkAdapter] returns PerformanceLevel:
    Let max_speed be 0 For each adapter in network:
    If adapter.speed is greater than max_speed:
    Set max_speed to adapter.speed If max_speed is greater than 10000:
    Return Extreme If max_speed is greater than 1000:
    Return High If max_speed is greater than 100:
    Return Medium Return Low

Note: Utility functions
Process called "detect_path_separator" returns String:
    Note: Mock path separator detection
    Let test_path be OS.get_current_working_directory() If String.contains with str as test_path and substring as "\\":
    Return "\\"
    Return "/"

Process called "detect_kernel_name" returns String:
    Let platform_name be detect_platform_name() Match platform_name:
    When "Windows":
    Return "NT"
    When "macOS":
    Return "Darwin"
    Otherwise:
    Return platform_name

Process called "detect_windows_version" returns String:
    Note: Mock Windows version detection
    Return "10.0.19045"

Process called "detect_linux_version" returns String:
    Note: Mock Linux version detection
    Return "5.15.0"

Process called "detect_macos_version" returns String:
    Note: Mock macOS version detection
    Return "13.5"

Process called "detect_windows_kernel_version" returns String:
    Return "10.0.19045.3448"

Process called "detect_linux_kernel_version" returns String:
    Return "5.15.0-86-generic"

Process called "detect_macos_kernel_version" returns String:
    Return "22.6.0"

Process called "detect_linux_distribution" returns String:
    Note: Mock Linux distribution detection
    Return "Ubuntu 22.04 LTS"

Process called "detect_windows_edition" returns String:
    Return "Windows 11 Pro"

Process called "get_architecture_indicators" returns List[String]:
    Let indicators be list Note: Mock architecture indicators
    Add "x86_64" to indicators
    Add "AMD64" to indicators Return indicators

